#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:11
msgid "Configuring the system clock"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><primary>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:14
msgid "clock"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><secondary>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:15
msgid "configuring"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:17
msgid ""
"This section discusses how to configure the <command>systemd-"
"timedated</command> system service, which configures system clock and "
"timezone."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:21
msgid ""
"Systemd provides a <command>timedatectl</command> utility which is used to "
"communicate with <command>systemd-timedated</command>. It can be used to set"
" the system clock in local time or UTC time, depending on the hardware clock"
" setting. By default, <command>systemd-timedated</command> will assume that "
"clock is set to UTC time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:27
msgid ""
"If you cannot remember whether or not the hardware clock is set to UTC, find"
" out by running the <userinput>hwclock --localtime --show</userinput> "
"command. This will display what the current time is according to the "
"hardware clock. If this time matches whatever your watch says, then the "
"hardware clock is set to local time. If the output from "
"<command>hwclock</command> is not local time, chances are it is set to UTC "
"time. Verify this by adding or subtracting the proper amount of hours for "
"the timezone to the time shown by <command>hwclock</command>. For example, "
"if you are currently in the MST timezone, which is also known as GMT -0700, "
"add seven hours to the local time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:38
msgid ""
"<command>systemd-timedated</command> reads "
"<filename>/etc/adjtime</filename>, and depending on the contents of the "
"file, it sets the clock to either UTC or local time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:42
msgid ""
"Create the <filename>/etc/adjtime</filename> file with the following "
"contents if your hardware clock is set to local time:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:45
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/adjtime &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>0.0 0 0.0\n"
"0\n"
"LOCAL</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/adjtime &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal>0.0 0 0.0\n"
"0\n"
"LOCAL</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:51
msgid ""
"If <filename>/etc/adjtime</filename> isn't present at first boot, <command"
">systemd-timedated</command> will assume that hardware clock is set to UTC "
"and adjust the file according to that."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:55
msgid ""
"If your clock is set to local time, tell <command>systemd-"
"timedated</command> about it by running the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:59
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>timedatectl set-local-rtc 1</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>timedatectl set-local-rtc 1</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:61
msgid ""
"<command>timedatectl</command> can also be used to change system time and "
"time zone."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:64
msgid "To change your current system time, issue:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>timedatectl set-time YYYY:MM:DD HH:MM:SS</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>timedatectl set-time YYYY:MM:DD HH:MM:SS</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:68
msgid "Hardware clock will also be updated accordingly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:70
msgid "To change your current time zone, issue:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:72
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>timedatectl set-timezone TIMEZONE</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>timedatectl set-timezone TIMEZONE</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:74
msgid "You can get list of available time zones by running:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>timedatectl list-timezones</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>timedatectl list-timezones</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/clock.xml:78
msgid ""
"Please note that <command>timedatectl</command> command can be used only on "
"a system booted with systemd."
msgstr ""
